Brazil Pharma Plans to Raise Up to $328 Million in Initial Public Offering

-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 
2011-06-07T09:04:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/brazil-pharma-plans-to-raise-up-to-328-million-in-initial-public-offering.html
Brazil Pharma SA, the pharmacy unit
of Banco BTG Pactual SA, is seeking to raise as much as 519.8
million reais ($328 million) in an initial public offering.  Brazil Pharma plans to sell as many as 27 million shares,
including possible supplementary offerings, according to a
prospectus published today in Sao Paulo-based newspaper Valor
Economico. The stock may be priced at 16.25 reais to 19.25
reais, Brazil Pharma said.  BTG Pactual is coordinating the offering with Morgan
Stanley and Banco Bradesco BBI SA. The stock is likely to be
priced on June 22 and will start trading June 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price in London at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  